  "prompt": "If I delete someone's conversation (old msgs + new unread message) on WhatsApp without reading it and without opening their chat window, will they receive blue ticks?",
  "response": "If you delete someone's conversation on WhatsApp without reading it and without opening their chat window, they will not receive blue ticks. Blue ticks on WhatsApp indicate that the message has been read, and if you delete the conversation without opening it, the sender will not be notified that you have read their message.\n\nHowever, keep in mind that if you have read receipts enabled and you accidentally open the chat window or preview the message in the notification, the sender might receive blue ticks, indicating that you have read their message. To avoid this, make sure to delete the conversation without interacting with the chat or the notification.",
